Subject: Bolesaww, Lower Silesian Voivodeship 
To: Edith
Content:
Bolesaww [blswavuf] (German: Wilhelmsthal) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Stronie lskie, within Kodzko County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. Prior to 1945 it was in Germany. It lies approximately 5 kilometres (3mi) south of Stronie lskie, 27 kilometres (17mi) south-east of Kodzko, and 98 kilometres (61mi) south of the regional capital Wrocaw. The village has a population of 250.
